<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6dc2ea7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53705"><num value="53705">§ 53705.</num><heading> Pledge of United States Government</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6dc2ea8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53705/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Full Faith and Credit</inline>.—</heading><content>The full faith and credit of the United States Government is pledged to the payment of a guarantee made under this chapter, for both principal and interest, including interest (as may be provided for in the guarantee) accruing between the date of default under a guaranteed obligation and the date of payment in full of the guarantee.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6dc2ea9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53705/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Incontestability</inline>.—</heading><content>A guarantee or commitment to guarantee made under this chapter is conclusive evidence of the eligibility of the obligation for the guarantee. The validity of a guarantee or commitment to guarantee made under this chapter is incontestable.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6dc2eaa-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1606">120 Stat. 1606</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/163/dC/tXXXV/s3507/a/1/C">Pub. L. 109–163, div. C, title XXXV, § 3507(a)(1)(C)</ref>, <date date="2006-01-06">Jan. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/3555">119 Stat. 3555</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/110/181/dC/tXXXV/s3522/b">Pub. L. 110–181, div. C, title XXXV, § 3522(b)</ref>, <date date="2008-01-28">Jan. 28, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/598">122 Stat. 598</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
